Package: gwas2crispr
Type: Package
Title: GWAS-to-CRISPR Data Pipeline for High-Throughput SNP Target Extraction
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Othman S. I.", family = "Mohammed", email = "admin@leopard.ly", role = c("aut", "cre")), person(given = "LEOPARD.LY LTD", role = "cph"))
Description: Provides a reproducible pipeline to extract, process, and export
    significant genome-wide association study (GWAS) single nucleotide
    polymorphisms (SNPs) for a human trait or disease identified by its
    Experimental Factor Ontology (EFO) identifier. Given a trait and a p-value
    threshold, the package retrieves significant SNPs from the GWAS Catalog,
    annotates their gene context, and can write a harmonized metadata table
    ('CSV'), genomic intervals in the Browser Extensible Data ('BED') format,
    and sequences in the 'FASTA' file format with user-defined flanking regions
    for clustered regularly interspaced short palindromic repeats (CRISPR)
    guide design. See Buniello et al. (2019) <doi:10.1093/nar/gkz895> and
    Sollis et al. (2023) <doi:10.1093/nar/gkac1010> for the GWAS Catalog, and
    Malone et al. (2010) <doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/btq648> for EFO, and Jinek et al. (2012) <doi:10.1126/science.1225829> for CRISPR methodology.
